==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sprint
<hw>Sprint</hw> <pr>(spr⟦icr⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Sprinted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Sprinting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Sprunt</er>.]</ety> <def>To run very rapidly; to run at full
speed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A runner [in a quarter-mile race] should be able to
<qex>sprint</qex> the whole way.</q> <rj><qau>Encyc.
Brit.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sprint</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sprint
<hw>Sprint</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of sprinting; a run of a
short distance at full speed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sprint race</b></col>, <cd>a foot race at the highest
running speed; -- usually limited to distances under a quarter of a
mile.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sprinter</ent>⟦br⟧
